 <Playwright.Components.SpecialConditions.XenotypeSwap.ReplacedBy>replaced by</Playwright.Components.SpecialConditions.XenotypeSwap.ReplacedBy>
 <Playwright.Components.SpecialConditions.XenotypeSwap.Add>Add replacement</Playwright.Components.SpecialConditions.XenotypeSwap.Add>
 <Playwright.Components.SpecialConditions.XenotypeSwap.AddCustom>Add custom replacement</Playwright.Components.SpecialConditions.XenotypeSwap.AddCustom>
 <Playwright.Components.SpecialConditions.XenotypeSwap.Help>Quick and dirty xenotype replacement. Replaces the chosen xenotypes with other ones when the pawn is generated (does nothing when implanting an existing pawn). While this does work, I recommend using WorldBuilder or Xenotype Spawn Control instead for non-custom xenotypes.

Use "Add replacement" to replace a xenotype in the game with another xenotype in the game, or "Add custom replacement" to replace a xenotype in the game with one of your own saved custom xenotypes.

Example: this can replace all Neanderthals with Hussars, all Baseliners with Genies, or all Sanguophages with your own custom Sanguophage.

Note: The game demands that some generated pawns are capable of certain things, like faction leaders being capable of violence. If this fails, the game will generate a pawn normally and log a harmless error.

Raids will respect xenotypes when calculating raid points, so replacing one xenotype with another will not result in underpowered/overpowered raids.</Playwright.Components.SpecialConditions.XenotypeSwap.Help>

